**Seeking REAL ZUMBA INSTRUCTORS ages 20-35 for a non-union commercial shooting in Vancouver, BC!**

**CALLBACKS:** October 30, 2025

**WARDROBE:** November 4, 2025

(Twitter), Reddit, Mobile Communication Apps, Software and Gaming (incl.AR/VR Hardware).

**PLEASE EMAIL US IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS:** kkstreetcasting@gmail.com

***PLEASE DO NOT SEND ANY MESSAGES THROUGH FACEBOOK**

items.title: Let's welcome our new members!

items.text:
Hey filmy friends!!!

Community is a lot like a garden. If you want a healthy, vibrant one, you gotta cultivate that shit. You gotta tend it and care for it. So, let's really dig in and build the most incredible community/garden we possibly can. 

This means ya gotta get off your tuchas and show up. Show up for events and meetings and elections and programs and festivals and screenings and all the hooooo ha. 

You want people to come see your project, ya gotta go see theirs. 
You want people to hire you, ya gotta get out and meet the people hiring. 
You want to find great people to be on your set, then ya gotta get out and meet the people you want to hire. 

Get involved!!! Sign up for shit!! Have fun!!! Make cool stuff!!! 

The next fun thing we have is this Friday. The CFVA is hosting a Halloween party. You can dress up or not, but be there! Show up. Play. Engage. Connect. It's how we will grow CO Film into something undeniable!!!! 

Come find me and say hi. I'll be busting ghosts!

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of text that says 'CFVA SAVE THE DATE! HALLOWEEN ALLOWEE PARTY THE ANNUAL CFVA HALLOWEEN PARTY! FRIDAY, OCTOBER 24TH- WULF LUV STUDIOS 1516 Teller Street Lakewood, CO 80214 7PM-11PM'

items.text:
Hello Everyone!

My name is Rayonna Price and I am writer/director for a short film called 'Cursed'. It is a University of Colorado Denver film.

A woman suffers through a rough day, will she get through unscathed or will someone lose their head?

Dionne and Jason have been casted for, however, we still are still looking for our Nadine and Bryce. All locations are in central Denver, and our filming dates are November 13th-16th. Transportation can be provided.

To audition and find sides follow the google link here: https://forms.gle/KJJKmE3bG3HgYHkDA

Actors will be reimbursed, please audition we would love to have you apart of production!

Thank you!

items.text:
Casting Call: The Chaos

We are seeking talented and passionate actors (18+) to join our exciting new Indie project! This is a unique opportunity to be part of a creative and collaborative production, utilizing **virtual production techniques** and **green screen technology**.

Requirements:

- Must be 18 years or older

- Comfortable performing in front of a green screen

- Enthusiastic about participating in an indie, creative-driven environment

Details:

- This is an unpaid project, but it offers a great chance to build your portfolio and gain experience in virtual production.

- Flexible scheduling for green screen scenes.

- A fantastic opportunity to work with a dedicated team on a passion project.

-IMDb Credit

If you're excited to bring unique characters to life in an innovative way, we'd love to hear from you!

To Apply:

Please submit a headshot, resume, and a brief video introduction.

They do not have to be professional!

We are looking for someone to portray these characters!

More information will be given after submission:

Chris presents himself as calm, confident, and even comforting. His tone is measured ‚Äî he doesn‚Äôt command; he invites. He speaks like a leader or preacher, someone used to controlling a room through subtle persuasion rather than force. The steady eyes, careful pouring, and soft assurances suggest someone who knows how to perform sincerity.

Underneath the calm surface, there‚Äôs a manipulative intent.

Chris Myers (African American ages 20-30)

https://form.jotform.com/250471188877166

Dates

We are offering 700 to 800   per week fuel on the road and accommodation allowance when required.

We‚Äôre currently casting for **two main characters** in our upcoming **third-year short film project**, a **horror-comedy** shooting in **Coventry** (with the possibility of additional locations ‚Äî confirmed actors will be informed in advance).

This is an **unpaid student production**, but we will **cover travel costs and catering** during filming days.

We‚Äôre looking for **dedicated and enthusiastic actors** who are passionate about working on creative projects and open to collaborating with a student film crew.

If you‚Äôre interested, please email **davist11@coventry.ac.uk** with your **headshot, showreel (if available), and a short bio**.
Once you get in touch, I‚Äôll send over **all the details about the audition process** and what to expect.

We‚Äôre aiming to **lock in our final cast by January**, so please make sure you‚Äôre available for the filming period mentioned above.

This is a great opportunity to gain on-set experience, expand your portfolio, and be part of a fun and ambitious student film! üé•‚ú®

items.text:
Hey guys! We are now enrolling for November classes! There is still some availability in each class, though they're filling quickly. We'd love to have you with us! To register or ask any questions: Please email me at SarahDowlingCasting@gmail.com and put November Classes in the subject line! 

**

We are now registering for our November Zoom workshops and would love for you to join us! Classes are kept intentionally small to maximize the workshop time and provide feedback to each person throughout the class! We look at the back-end of casting software - what a casting director sees when you send your tapes and materials via email or through services like Actors Access, and what the client sees when your material is sent to them! We also cover Scene Study and Improv, and all things business related - auditions, materials, self-tapes etc.  

 I am a 20-year veteran casting director.  My classes are very much tailored to the students who are in them each month. We delve into commercial casting: how to figure out the storyboards and scripts you're sent to audition, how to figure out the tone they're looking for and how to make sure your tapes look like they should for submission. We also do a deep dive into film casting: how to discern the tone and pacing of the script, how to fully inhabit the character and how to make sure your tape captures all of it. 

**This is a business class (taught by a casting director with 20+ yeas experience) offering practical real-life to help actors get representation, widen their representation into other markets, and get more auditions, call backs and bookings.

Please let me know if you have any questions or would like to join us! You can email me at SarahDowlingCasting@gmail.com with any questions or to register! Let me know which day or days are best for you when you email!  Looking forward to working with you! 

Thanks so much,

Sarah

items.text:
MERIVENTS is Hiring!

We‚Äôre excited to assemble our Dream Team of talented professionals for iconic NYC events like SNL wrap parties, movie premieres, and sporting events.

**Building Our Dream Team**

At Amerivents, we are committed to assembling and empowering a "Dream Team" of talented individuals who bring diverse skills, shared values, and a unified purpose to every endeavor. Much like a championship sports team, we believe that our collective success is built on the strength and collaboration of our team members, each contributing their unique expertise to achieve exceptional results.

**Now Hiring FRONT OF HOUSE:**
* Catering Hospitality Staff
* Servers
* Bartenders
* Captains

**Now Hiring BACK OF HOUSE:**
* Dishwasher
* Utility
* Grill Cook
* Line Cook

**Requirements:**

2+ years of catering or high-end retail experience

You must be 18 or older

**Next Steps:**
1. Complete the interview survey here: [https://forms.gle/r3B2ib3kssxRfF5v8](https://forms.gle/r3B2ib3kssxRfF5v8)
2. Visit[ www.amerivents.com](http://www.amerivents.com/) and click ‚ÄúApply‚Äù (mention ‚ÄúCORE-NYC‚Äù in the referral box).

**Why Amerivents?**
* Fast-paced, exciting, and team-oriented work environment
* Flexible schedules‚Äîyou choose your availability!
* Gain unforgettable experiences in the hospitality industry
* Experience unique and inspiring event locations!

**What We‚Äôre Looking For:**
* 2+ years of catering or high-end retail experience
* Professional, adaptable, and radiate positivity team players
* Composure under pressure and ability to adapt to dynamic environments
* Flexible and reliable team players who can seamlessly adjust to varying roles and tasks
* Ability to lift 50 lbs and stand for extended periods

**To Our Team:**
We offer the chance to pursue your passions while contributing to a company that values your unique talents and provides the support you need to excel.

We look forward to hearing from you!

**This is not an official job offer**

items.text:
The new Online Casting Room is here‚Äîand we‚Äôre offering something special to the first people to try it out!

The Online Casting Room simplifies and streamlines the casting process by moving it online. It‚Äôs an exclusively Canadian service that filmmakers and casting directors can use to build the cast of their dreams, and that actors can use to find their next role. Whether you‚Äôre emerging or established film talent, the Online Casting Room is here to save you time, money, and energy while extending your reach beyond your geographic location.

All you need to do to create a casting call is fill in a few quick prompts. Then, the choice to host live auditions or review self-tapes is yours. Built-in collaborative features mean your entire casting team can be involved in the process, enabling you to share notes, provide feedback, and exchange messages‚Äîall within our platform!

Our Special Offer: While right now, all access to cinewoo is free, we will be rolling out paid subscription tiers in the next future. To thank the early supporters of the Online Casting Room, we‚Äôre offering an extended 2-year free access period to our platform to everybody who posts a casting call between now and December 31, 2025 (effective when paid subscriptions are introduced). 

You have everything to gain, and nothing to lose‚Äîstep into the Online Casting Room at [www.cinewoo.com](http://www.cinewoo.com) today!

CASTING NOTICE ‚Äî VANCOUVER
Seeking** cool looking, camera-friendly adults** (all adult ages welcome) **based in Vancouver** for a short shoot.

**WHEN:** November 4
**WHERE:** Outdoor spots around Stanley Park (exact meet point shared upon booking), and potentially indoors as well at a studio.
**SCENES:** Relaxed, music-centric visuals ‚Äî reclining in scenic nature locations and listening to music

**bright colors in your own wardrobe (you need to come camera ready) is a plus!

**RATE:** **$150** for **2‚Äì3 hours**

**TO APPLY:** Email **mylcasting@gmail.com** with:
* Your name and age
* A recent photo (waist-up or full-body)
* A brief note on availability and any on-camera experience (optional)

Local Vancouver applicants only. No acting experience required.

We‚Äôre looking for a passionate and creative teacher to join our After-School Musical Theatre Program based at a local elementary school in Pasadena.

 ‚Ä¢ Schedule: Once a week, 1-hour class

 ‚Ä¢ Students: Kindergarten & 1st Grade

 ‚Ä¢ Goal: Prepare a short performance for families and fellow students in April

 ‚Ä¢ Focus areas: Creativity, focus, teamwork, confident stage presence, basic choreography, and simple songs

 ‚Ä¢ Compensation: $70 per class

 ‚Ä¢ Start date: ASAP

‚ú® Experience working with young children is a must!

üé≠ Please send your resume/portfolio and contact info ‚Äî I‚Äôd love to connect!

üì© Direct message me or feel free to email me at em@bigstepsla.com

üì±You can also reach out via Instagram @bigstepsla

Looking forward to hearing from you!

CASTING CALL ‚Äì TV SHOW: DON‚ÄôT GET CATFISHED (SERIES 2)

The hit Channel 4.0 entertainment show is BACK and casting for Season 2!

LOCATION: London Studio

DATES: Thursday 13th or Friday 14th November 2025

PAID

We're looking for single men (28+) and single women (25+) who want their chance to bag a date with one of the UK‚Äôs top creators.

If you‚Äôre a Confident Queen, Rizz Royalty, It Girl, Zaddie, or a Reformed F-boy, and you serve main character energy, this show wants you in the mix.

THE TWIST:

Among the five mysterious blind "dates" (whose voices are disguised and identities hidden) are undercover friends of the creator, secretly trying to trick their way to a free date night. Can you tell who‚Äôs real?

CASTING CALL FOR A STUDENT SHORT-FILM!

Hi hi! My name is Megan Veto and I am a student at the Aurora Community College and will serve as the Writer/Director of this project. I am in need of actors/actresses for my Production 1 project! This will be unpaid, though I will provide anyone interested with a final version of the film. You will also be fed, so please let me know of any allergies or specific diets you may have!

Title: On the Rocks
Genre: Romantic Comedy
Logline: An angry bride walks into a bar and shakes up Ramos‚Äôs day.

SHOOTING DAYS: November 8th (10a - 6p) - 9th (1p - 7p)

LOCATION: 9075 E Lowry Blvd Denver, CO 80230

CHARACTERS:

-Ramos: The bartender. Late 20‚Äôs - early 30‚Äôs. Calm, cool, and collected. Takes care of his patrons. Wardrobe will be all black and a black button-up shirt.

-Sarah: The angry bride. Mid - late 20‚Äôs. Feisty, knows what she wants, but eventually softens under Ramos‚Äôs care. Please let me know what your dress size is so I can find a bride‚Äôs dress that fits! üòÅ

-Mike: The ex. Mid - 20‚Äôs. Flustered, desperately looking for Sarah. Cheated. Wardrobe will be black slacks and a nice white button-down shirt.

-Ruth: Sarah‚Äôs mom. 50‚Äôs. Helps Mike look for Sarah. Wardrobe will be a nice dress.

Please email me at megveto96@gmail.com with your headshot and demo reel, I will send you the script to read over.

Thank you so muc

Dream & Dazzle Parties is growing and on the lookout for more energetic, reliable, and imaginative performers to join our fun, dynamic team! We predominantly provide princess performers for children‚Äôs parties across London and surrounding areas, but we also offer other entertainment opportunities so we would love to hear from you if you meet our requirements! üåü 

We‚Äôre especially keen to hear from people with:
üé≠ Performing or teaching experience 
üéâ Experience working with children and/or leading workshops for children 
üöó A driver‚Äôs license (a bonus but not essential)
üí´ A passion for creating unforgettable memories for families

We believe kids should see performers who reflect the wonderfully diverse world they live in- so we warmly welcome applications from performers of all backgrounds, particularly those from underrepresented communities.

If you think you would make a great addition to our team, we‚Äôd love to hear from youüåü
üì© Please send your CV and a recent headshot to janelle@dreamanddazzle.co.uk

items.text:
*Casting Call for a short dance film shooting early next year January 24th and 25th in VANCOUVER. 
A short dance film expressing the importance of forgiveness of youth, bringing awareness to issues such as mental health, identity struggles and substance addiction in youth culture.
This is a volunteer position, but all food, studio rehearsal space and credits will be provided.
Video clips, photographs and stills will be provided as well for portfolio/demo reels to all dancers.

Requirements:
Must have contemporary dance experience and comfortable in front of camera.
Have reliable transportation to set/rehearsals
Age ranging from 19-27
Must be available BOTH shoot dates and additionally some time before the shoot for rehearsals!

DUE DATE FOR SUBMISSION: NOVEMBER 6TH 
Please submit a headshot/recent photo of yourself and a demo reel or video of your dancing.
Send all applications or questions to:
sodamihong@gmail.com 
shenassakayla@gmail.com

F√ºr meinen kommenden Kurzfilm ‚ÄûZwischen Licht und Schatten‚Äú (Drehort gebe ich noch bekannt) am 10.01 und 11.01 suche ich noch engagierte Mitwirkende:

üé¨ Regie

Ich suche eine/n Regisseur:in, die/der Lust hat, gemeinsam mit mir diesen emotional intensiven Kurzfilm umzusetzen. Das Projekt ist charaktergetrieben und bewegt sich zwischen innerem Konflikt, famili√§rer Bindung und Selbstfindung.

Erfahrung ist w√ºnschenswert, aber kein Muss ‚Äî wichtiger ist Leidenschaft, Teamgeist und Gesp√ºr f√ºr authentisches Schauspiel.

üé≠ Rollen

üë©‚Äçü¶∞ Lucy (ca. 25‚Äì28 Jahre)

‚Äì Stellas beste Freundin

‚Äì herzlich, empathisch, gute Zuh√∂rerin

‚Äì ruhig, aber pr√§sent, gibt Stella Halt

‚Äì Spielalter: ca. 26 Jahre

‚Äì Drehtage: [1‚Äì2]

‚Äì Keine Gage, aber Verpflegung + Material f√ºr Showreel

üë¶ Felix (Spielalter 20-22 Jahre)

‚Äì Stellas j√ºngerer Bruder

‚Äì ehemals drogenabh√§ngig, heute sehr zur√ºckhaltend, manchmal verschlossen

‚Äì steht im Zwiespalt zwischen Angst und St√§rke

‚Äì hat Respekt vor Viktor (dem B√∂sewicht , drogendealer), aber kann sich im entscheidenden Moment behaupten

‚Äì Drehtage: 10.01-11.01

Kurzinhalt

Die 25-j√§hrige Stella lebt zur√ºckgezogen, misstrauisch gegen√ºber M√§nnern und misstrauisch

gegen√ºber Gef√ºhlen. Als sie im Park den sportlichen, offenen Nick kennenlernt, entsteht eine

leise N√§he ‚Äì doch Stella blockt jeden Ann√§herungsversuch ab.

W√§hrend sie langsam Vertrauen zu Nick fasst, ger√§t ihr Bruder Felix in ernste Schwierigkeiten:

Er schuldet Victor, einem gef√§hrlichen Drogendealer, 5.000 Euro. Victor bedroht Felix und sucht

schlie√ülich auch Stella auf, um an sein Geld zu kommen.

Eines Abends eskaliert die Situation. Victor lauert Stella auf ‚Äì und als Nick hinzukommt, versucht

er, sie zu sch√ºtzen. Er h√§lt ihm sein Portemonnaie mit 300 Euro hin, um Zeit zu gewinnen. Doch

Victor wird w√ºtend: ‚ÄûIch will mein Geld ‚Äì oder einer von euch stirbt!‚Äú

Nick sagt zu Stella, sie solle laufen. Zitternd flieht sie und versteckt sich hinter einem Baum.

Dann kommt es zum Kampf zwischen Nick und Victor. In einem verzweifelten Moment wird

Victor im Bauch verletzt und bricht zusammen. Als Stille einkehrt, tritt Stella hervor, ruft ‚ÄûNick!‚Äú,

l√§uft zu ihm, und beide fallen sich unter Tr√§nen in die Arme. Ein Moment zwischen Dunkelheit

und Hoffnung ‚Äì und vielleicht der Beginn einer echten Heilung.

Drehtort noch unbekannt Max im Umkreis von 200 km  von Nordhorn

üóìÔ∏è Drehzeitraum: Januar 2026

üí¨  ‚Äì gern per PN oder E-Mail an [de.pascalis1990@web.de] kontaktieren

Hi!

We‚Äôre casting for a short film shooting in Nottingham this November.

üé¨ Lead role ‚Äì Oliver (male, 20‚Äì28 y.o.)

A thoughtful, creative young man living in Nottingham whose story quietly intersects with the war in Ukraine. No combat scenes ‚Äî the focus is emotional and character-driven.

We‚Äôre also casting:

 ‚Ä¢2‚Äì3 young men (friends, 20‚Äì28 y.o.)
 ‚Ä¢1 young woman (sister, 20‚Äì28 y.o.)
 ‚Ä¢Mother and father (50‚Äì60 y.o.)

The film explores youth, distance, and the impact of war ‚Äî seen through parallel stories between the UK and Ukraine.

üé• This is a volunteer project (drinks & snacks provided).

OPEN CASTING CALL

Rose Waite Studio are looking for inter-generational pairs who share a genuine love of theatre to feature in a filmed story for The Guardian and a paid partner. You will get the chance to watch a live theatre show from the opera box at one of Lloyd Webber‚Äôs theatres.

You could be a grandparent and grandchild, friends or colleagues etc. who share a genuine love of theatre to feature in a filmed story for The Guardian and a paid partner. 

You‚Äôll need to be based in or near London. 

This is a paid opportunity. 

If you‚Äôd like to be filmed sharing your story, email stories@rosewaite.com with details of your story together and why theatre matters to you both.

Shoot dates: 24 & 25 November

Thank you!

# (Paid) Casting for George Fox University Student Film, (Hillsboro, Oregon)

We are a group of George Fox students shooting a short film at the Airplane Home for our Location Production class, looking for a total of three non-union actors.

Project Title: Clearing The Air

Location: Airplane Home: 15270 SW Holly Hill Rd, Hillsboro, OR 97123

Safety Considerations: Dress for potential rain and cold weather. Several cats roam around the area, so be weary if you have any allergies. The actor that plays Jean will hold a non functional prop firearm.

 Shoot Dates: 10/28/2025 and 10/30/2025, 2:00PM - 9:00PM

Age Requirement: 18 and over

Pay: 50$ per day

You will receive a collection of your scenes to include in your reel.

Synopsis: Lost in the woods, siblings Gertie and Hudson come upon an airplane containing valuables. The sister aims to ransack the plane, while her brother urges her against it. Upon the return of the airplane‚Äôs resident, Jean, the sister attempts to escape with her spoils by attacking Jean from behind while her brother serves as a distraction. Her plan is thwarted by Jean, who catches her in the act, and Hudson, who reveals her presence and forces her to return what she stole. Once the two parties agree to part ways, it is revealed that Jean is a fugitive with a reward for her capture, worth more than anything the siblings could‚Äôve stolen.

Character Breakdown

(Antagonist) Jean: A perceptive older woman with a soft face but a hardened demeanor, a criminal past, and a lifetime of secrets behind her eyes.

Age: The character is meant to be in her early sixties, but her age isn't a strict guideline.

(Protagonist) Hudson: A thoughtful late teen with dark hair, an anxious posture, and a subdued retro rock styling, who has a tendency to let others walk over him.

He is the younger brother to Gertie.

"Think William Miller in Almost Famous but more frazzled and sarcastic."

Age: Roughly 18-19

(Protagonist) Gertie: An outdoorsy, has-it-all-together college girl with a ‚ÄúKaren Carpenter‚Äù fashion sense, a hidden impulsive nature, and a proclivity toward not seeing beyond her own scope.

Age: Around 20-21 years old

Audition sides are in the link below. Please record your auditions and send them to Bronson Revilla at brevilla21@georgefox.edu.

[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdV5_ZnMYF6723lCAGBG3bluhEtj3u9prGwzw-Q1BcY/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1JdV5_ZnMYF6723lCAGBG3bluhEtj3u9prGwzw-Q1BcY/edit?usp=sharing)

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì Gaunt Man / Doctor (Dual Role) in Short Film *****The Damned Spot***

**Production Title:** *The Damned Spot*
**Company:** SWRCO Studios / Racetothefinishline Studios
**Location:** Atlanta, GA
**Union Status:** Non-Union
**Compensation:** $200 flat rate (2 half-days)
**Role: Gaunt Man / Doctor (Male, 40s‚Äì80s)**

**Character Description:**
This is a dual-performance role. The **Doctor** appears grounded, calm, and professional ‚Äî a clinician trying to reassure his patient. The **Gaunt Man** is his nightmarish double: unsettling, skeletal in presence, and haunting. The shift between the two is central to the film‚Äôs psychological horror.

**Requirements:**
* Male, age range 40‚Äì85
* Ability to portray both a grounded, realistic character and a chilling, silent presence
* Strong facial expression and physical control ‚Äî much of the horror relies on stillness and presence
* Comfortable with light makeup (pale complexion, under-eye work) and basic VFX markers
**Filming Commitment:**
* 2 Half-Days
* $200 flat rate
**To Apply:**

Please submit:
* Headshot and resume (or reel, if available)
* Brief note about prior experience in psychological drama or horror
* Contact information

Send submissions to: **studio@swrco.us**
**Deadline:** **10-24-2025**

SATURDAY 25TH OCTOBER
JHANAK

Follow  Updates for the fastest updates

Parasar tells the villagers that he is the father of Nutan‚Äôs baby and that the child will stay in the village. One villager supports him, saying that since Nutan is Parasar‚Äôs wife, no one has the right to punish them. The village head also agrees. Bua refuses to accept Nutan and the baby, but Parasar says he has found a new house where he will live with them. Kanka mocks him, but Parasar tells her to be quiet, and the village head orders her to leave.

Later, Nutan questions Parasar about his decision. He explains that he never said she was his wife. He only gave his name to the baby so that the child would have an identity. He tells her that he has no plans to marry her. His friends tease him for becoming a father, and he laughs, inviting them to a small celebration at his house. He then gives the baby to Kanka and tells her that the child needs her affection too.

Elsewhere, Jhimli tells Appu that they cannot live without her. Appu says she knows that and that is why she avoids Anjana. She asks them not to cry if she dies and tells Kajol to love Lalon with all her heart. Kajol says she will leave and never come back. Appu then admits that she does not want to die because it would break her parents‚Äô hearts.

Anjana offers to cook something for her, and everyone hugs Appu with love. Later, Lalon visits the Bose house looking very worried. Mrinalini and Anirudh ask about Appu‚Äôs medical reports. Lalon reveals that Appu has cancer and that her condition is serious. Anirudh is shocked and asks if anything can be done to save her. Lalon begs for help.

Back in the village, Parasar goes home and apologizes to Nutan. She tells him that his apology means nothing now. She asks why he planned a celebration and gave the baby to Kanka. Parasar explains that they need Kanka‚Äôs support. Nutan tells him that they should not meet in private anymore and says she will start working the next day. Parasar encourages her to interact with the villagers and move forward in life.

Nutan says the baby will not stay there forever. Parasar agrees and says he only helped her out of kindness, not responsibility. Nutan becomes upset because he keeps reminding her of that. When he asks about dinner, she replies that she will eat tomorrow. Parasar warns her not to test his patience or question his respect for her. He says he will not stay in her room because he has no right to and asks her not to insult him again.

At Lalon‚Äôs house, Appu‚Äôs parents and Anirudh come to visit her. Anjana hugs Appu tightly and cries, but Appu asks her not to. Kajol tries to calm her mother down. Lalon, filled with sadness, asks why God is punishing them. Anirudh decides to take Appu to Mumbai for treatment. Lalon offers money to help, but Anirudh says he will manage everything because he is Appu‚Äôs brother. He promises Appu that she will recover soon.

Later, Kanka brings the baby to Nutan and teasingly asks Parasar what he likes about her. Parasar says he will tell her later and asks her to prepare dinner. She refuses at first but agrees when he insists. Parasar then leaves for a meeting and asks Kanka to take care of Nutan. Nutan looks sad and wonders why her life is always full of difficulties.

üé¨ **CASTING CALL ‚Äì COVENTRY UNIVERSITY FINAL YEAR FILM** üé¨

We‚Äôre currently casting for **two main characters** in our upcoming **third-year short film project**, a **horror-comedy** shooting in **Coventry** (with the possibility of additional locations ‚Äî confirmed actors will be informed in advance).

üìÖ **Filming Period:** Mid-February to March 2026
üéûÔ∏è **Length:** Approx. 15 minutes
üé≠ **Genre:** Horror Comedy

This is an **unpaid student production**, but we will **cover travel costs and catering** during filming days.

We‚Äôre looking for **dedicated and enthusiastic actors** who are passionate about working on creative projects and open to collaborating with a student film crew.

If you‚Äôre interested, please email **davist11@coventry.ac.uk** with your **headshot, showreel (if available), and a short bio**.
Once you get in touch, I‚Äôll send over **all the details about the audition process** and what to expect.

We‚Äôre aiming to **lock in our final cast by January**, so please make sure you‚Äôre available for the filming period mentioned above.

This is a great opportunity to gain on-set experience, expand your portfolio, and be part of a fun and ambitious student film! üé•‚ú®

üì£üé¨ CASTING CALL - Short Period Drama 

We are casting for The Stuntman, a 3-minute period drama made as part of our final year at UWE Bristol. The film will be shot in Bristol in the week commencing 10th November 2025 (exact dates TBC). This is a student project, unpaid, but with expenses covered. The film is intended for university showcase and festival submission.

Story:
Set in 1920s Wiltshire, The Stuntman follows Ed Morris, a small-town silent cinema owner fighting to keep his theatre alive as the arrival of sound threatens to change film forever. With his fianc√©e Alice by his side, Ed stages one last ambitious stunt in the hope of saving his cinema - and their livelihood. A warm yet bittersweet drama about determination, passion and the march of technological change.

Roles:
Ed Morris (Lead, 28)
Charming, intelligent, and hardworking. Outwardly confident, but hiding a quiet desperation as he struggles to keep silent film alive. Needs strong screen presence and subtle emotional depth.

Alice Fardon (Lead, 22‚Äì23)
Ed‚Äôs fianc√©e. Feisty, loyal, and practical. She supports his dreams but occasionally shows frustration at his all-consuming determination.

Community Extras
Townsfolk gathering to watch Ed‚Äôs big stunt. A mix of ages. Families, workers and individuals. To capture the atmosphere of a 1920s local community.

Apply by: 1st November 2025
To Apply: Please send a headshot, CV (or Spotlight/Mandy link), and any showreel/self-tape to: Scarlet2.Gerry@live.uwe.ac.uk

Please include in email subject: THE STUNTMAN & NAME

items.text:
Genre: Romance/Drama

Logline: Soulmates bound from the beginning of time must navigate the blurred lines between dreams and reality to discover their destiny together.

Roles:

Atlas: 20s, Male

Atlas always feels the weight of the world on his shoulders. He understands more about life and the universe than most people, which doesn‚Äôt help his abilities to strike up a conversation and ends up making him look reserved and detached. Atlas feels everything from the rotation of the Earth to everything that is supposed to happen in the future. His connection with the world makes him patient, almost seeming like he is unable to act on his desires, because he knows what the future holds.

Luna: 20s, Female

Luna enjoys the complexities of figuring out what life is. She wants to follow her passions and figure out what they mean along the way. She isn‚Äôt the type to turn people away, but instead see what they change in her life. She is never afraid, takes her own mortality in her hands, and believes there is a right answer to everything. The spark of life is in her and she doesn‚Äôt want to let anything snuff it out. Her dreams start to show her the past and what the future holds for her.

Pierce: 20s, Male

Pierce is a constant. He is dating Luna. He never does anything unexpected. He has a very simplistic view of the world and events that occur outside of it don‚Äôt really concern him. He is steadfast in his decisions and never doubts who he is or what he is doing. You can always expect him to be around, but if things get deeper he will very quickly drown from the weight of his inexperience.

Production Company: pearscarfproductions

Writer/Director: Nathan Chelf

Cinematographer: Nate Coberly

Production Type: Independant

Contact Info: pearscarfproductions@gmail.com

Run Time: Short Film

Compensation: Negotiable, this is a low budget, self funded project.

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: We will be holding in person auditions this Saturday, October 25th from 9:00 AM until 2:00 PM at 3111 E Colfax Ave Denver, CO 80206. Please email us if you are interested and we will get you a time slot. If you are unable to make it in person please reach out and we will set up a virtual audition another time or send you information to do a self tape. For in person we would love to see a monologue and we will have you do cold readings from the script.

Shooting Schedule: We are planning to be filming in December, final dates will be confirmed based on the schedules of our cast.

Filming Locations: The Denver Metro Area

Thank you for taking the time to read through this and I hope to hear from you soon!

items.text:
¬∑ Title: This Side of Midnight

¬∑ Genre: Horror

¬∑ Logline: An eighteen-year-old girl must confront her inner demons, both real and metaphorical, as they test her to see if she is worthy of life itself after a brush with death.

¬∑ Role: Lilith ‚Äî Female, late teens to early 20s

A newly eighteen-year-old struggling with severe depression and suicidal thoughts. Intelligent, introspective, and haunted by her inner world. The emotional core of the story.

Note: Lead role. Must be comfortable portraying intense emotional states.

Zera ‚Äî Female, late teens to early 20s

Lilith‚Äôs best friend. Empathetic and determined, trying desperately to remind Lilith that she matters.

Dad ‚Äî Male, 40s‚Äì50s (flexible)

A concerned father trying to reconnect with his daughter after finding her following a suicide attempt. Must convey deep emotion with subtlety.

Mom ‚Äî Female, 40s‚Äì50s (flexible)

 A mother struggling to cope as her daughter begins to withdraw, stop eating, and lose hope.

Sibling ‚Äî Any gender (preferably male), 10‚Äì15 (flexible)

Appears in one scene. No speaking lines, but must express strong emotion through facial expression and presence.

Cashier ‚Äî Any gender/age

Background role, no speaking lines.

¬∑ Production Company: Cassidy Cheldelin ‚Äî Writer, Director, Videographer, Editor
Jess Lange ‚Äî Co-Director, Casting Director, Producer

¬∑ Production Type: Student Film

¬∑ Contact Information: Contact: Jess Lange ‚Äî escapemindproductions@gmail.com
Instagram: @escapemind.productions 

¬∑ Run Time: Short (16 minutes)

¬∑ Compensation: Unpaid

¬∑ Union Status: Non-Union

¬∑ Audition Information: 

Format: Digital Submission

Please record a 1‚Äì2 minute monologue of your choice (preferably horror or drama) that demonstrates emotional depth. Include your name, age, preferred email & phone number, and desired role in the email. Name, age, and role for slate. 

Lilith Auditions: Monologue may be up to 5 minutes or the attached scene from the screenplay.

Dad Auditions: May choose to perform from the attached scene.

Submit to: escapemindproductions@gmail.com
Deadline: November 5, 11:59 PM (MST)

¬∑ Shooting Schedule: Mid-November (before Thanksgiving) table read, 11/8/25 at 12 (MST), location upon casting

¬∑ Filming Location: Black Forest, CO, 80908 & Colorado Springs, CO, North Academy Blvd.

¬∑ Project Description:

Two filmmakers are passionate about exploring mental health through the lens of horror. While this is not a professional production, we approach the project with deep respect and dedication to the craft. This Side of Midnight follows Lilith as she confronts her literal demons and manifestations of her struggles with mental illness, who test her will to live. When she ultimately fails, she is tragically taken, symbolizing the devastating reality of losing the battle against one‚Äôs own mind.

Lilith and Dad Scene 

Int. BEDROOM - MORNING

The screen flickers to her dad, shaking her awake

Dad

Lilith! Wake up! Please- Please, breathe please.

Lilith sits up suddenly, her breathing is chaotic, and she is in fear.

Her dad sighs in relief

Dad

Oh, thank god you are ok. I was about to call 911. What happened??

LILITH (studdering)

I- I don't know

She looks around the room, noticing the empty pill bottle next to her pillow, and she erratically shoves it further underneath so as not to let her dad see.

LILITH

Must've just been too much melatonin..

Dad

You scared the crap out of me and you're mother. Zera too.

Lilith looks defeated as her father sits more formally on her bed.

Dad

That reminds me, you should probably call her. She was worried sick about you.

LILITH

I will- I will do that.

Dad (in relief)

Good. You missed the bus. I have to go to work n' can't drive you- so have the day off.

LiLITH (under her breath)

T-Thanks.

DAD

A mental Health day- y'know? You deserve it.

Lilith's expression doesn't change. Her dad stands up and begins to put on his jacket

DAD

Let me know if you need anything, okay?

Messages sent at messenger won‚Äôt be answered. Only e-mails , please.

Best Regards,

Marilena.
